author: DistroTube
description:
'which' prints the full path of executable commands.  In other words, it can tell you the location of a program's executable binary.

- Search $PATH and print the location of any matching executables:
  which program-name

- If multiple matching executables, print all:
  which -a program-name

- Read  aliases  from  stdin, reporting matching ones on stdout.
  alias | which -i some-alias

- Skip directories in $PATH that begin with a dot (hidden directories):
  which --skip-dot program-name

- Skip directories in $PATH that begin with a tilde (such as ~/home/user):
  which --skip-dot program-name
